Human Activity Recognition using Machine Learning

Pre-requisites:
    Python 3.5
    sklearn
    matplotlib
    numpy
    itertools
    time

Data:
    Folder F1(with files):
        Project.py
        X_train.txt,y_train.txt
        X_test.txt,y_test.txt
        activity_labels.txt

Running the Code:
    1. Open the Terminal(on mac) or command prompt(Windows)
    2. Change directory to F1 folder using command cd
    3. Type "python Project.py"

Results:
    It runs 3 different classification Algorithms (Decision Tree, Multi Layer Perceptron Classifier, Logistic Regression)
    on the test data and find following metrics:
        1. Mean Squared Error
        2. Accuracy
        3. Confusion Matrix


